{
  "stem": "19923.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I always looked in the mirror and I could never figure out how he could tell if I was Jewish by looking at my nose.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But evidently, the Jew-- the Jews were singled out as being recognizable because they had a bump in their nose.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Germans, you could-- would go down the street and identify you and say, that a-- that's a Juden by his nose.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the-- we became conscious of the fact that we were singled out as different from the others and that we were not the same and were not allowed to do the same things.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- I don't remember if I ever went to a public school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think I went there-- no, I don't-- I never went.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went to kindergarten that was a Jewish kindergarten.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I knew I was not allowed to go in public school, so I went to a Jewish school, predominantly for Jewish people because they would not allow children.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when I was old enough to go to school, they would not allow Jewish children to go to public schools.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We did observe the holidays.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We observed-- I-- I do recall that when we ate for Sukkot, we would go to the roof of the apartment.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there-- there was sort of a-- an enclosed space like a shed on the apartment roof and we would use that for eating.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we would go up there and it would be decorated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the men could only eat, the women had to serve the food.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went up there to eat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --I remember that the Passover dinners were long and drawn out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was nothing like the way we do it now.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
